<p>Ben Graham did thisâ€¦Ben Franklin did this before him. Ben Graham in his low teensâ€¦looked aroundâ€¦he looked at the people who he admired and he said, you know, â€œI want to be admire, so why donâ€™t I just behave like them?â€ He found that there is nothing impossible about behaving like them. Similarly, he did the same thing on the reverse side in terms of getting rid of those qualities.</p>

