<p>Buffett: I likeâ€¦I like businesses I can understand. Letâ€™s start with that. That narrows down about 90%. There are all kinds of thing I donâ€™t understand, but fortunately there is enough I do understand. You have this big wide world out there, almost every company publicly owned. So you have all American businesses practically available to you. To start with, then it makes sense to go with things that you think you can understand. You can understand something. I can understand this! (Buffett is holding a tin of cherry-favored Cola) You can understand this, everybody can understand this! This is a product that basically hasnâ€™t changed when they take out the cherry. You know, since 1886, or whatever it was, it is a simple business. Itâ€™s not an easy business, I donâ€™t want a business that is easy for competitors. I want a business with a moat around it. I want a very valuable castle in the middle. Then I want the duke whoâ€™s in charge of that castle to be honest and hardworking and able. Then I want a big moat around the castle.</p>

<p><br /></p>

<p>æŠ¤åŸæ²³å¯ä»¥æ˜¯å¾ˆå¤šä¸œè¥¿ã€‚å…¬å¸çš„æŠ¤åŸæ²³â€¦æ¯”å¦‚åƒæˆ‘ä»¬çš„æ±½è½¦ä¿é™©å…¬å¸ï¼Œæ”¿åºœå‘˜å·¥ä¿é™©å…¬å¸ï¼Œæ˜¯ä½ä»·ã€‚æˆ‘çš„æ„æ€æ˜¯ï¼Œäººä»¬å¿…é¡»è¦ä¹°æ±½è½¦ä¿é™©ã€‚æ‰€ä»¥æ¯ä¸ªäººåŸºæœ¬ä¸Šæ˜¯è¦ä¸ºæ¯ä¸€è¾†è½¦ä¹°ä¸€åˆ†ä¿é™©â€¦æˆ–è€…æ¯ä¸€ä¸ªå¸æœºã€‚æˆ‘ä¸èƒ½ç»™ä¸€ä¸ªäººå–20ä»½ï¼Œä½†æ˜¯ä»–ä»¬å¿…é¡»è¦ä¹°ä¸€ä»½ã€‚é‚£ä»–ä»¬ä¼šé€‰å“ªä¸€ä»½ä¿é™©ï¼Ÿä»–ä»¬ä¼šæŒ‰ç…§æœåŠ¡å’Œä»·æ ¼æ¥é€‰æ‹©ã€‚å¤§éƒ¨åˆ†äººä¼šå‡è®¾æœåŠ¡æ˜¯å‡ ä¹ä¸€æ ·çš„ï¼Œæˆ–è€…å·®ä¸å¤šçš„ã€‚æ‰€ä»¥æˆ‘ä»¬åšçš„å°±æ˜¯ä»·æ ¼ï¼æˆ‘éœ€è¦æˆä¸ºä½ä»·æä¾›è€…ã€‚è¿™æ˜¯æˆ‘çš„æŠ¤åŸæ²³ã€‚æˆ‘çš„ä»·æ ¼è¿›ä¸€æ­¥çš„ä½äºä»–äººï¼Ÿé‚£æˆ‘å°±ç›¸å½“äºåœ¨æŠ¤åŸæ²³é‡Œæ”¾äº†å‡ åªé²¨é±¼ã€‚ä»»ä½•æ—¶å€™ï¼Œå¦‚æœä½ æœ‰ä¸€ä¸ªå¾ˆå¥½çš„åŸå ¡ï¼Œæ€»æœ‰äººåœ¨å¤–é¢æƒ³è¦æ”»å‡»å®ƒï¼Œæ‹¿èµ°å®ƒã€‚æˆ‘æƒ³è¦æˆ‘èƒ½çœ‹æ‡‚çš„åŸå ¡ï¼Œä½†è¿™åŸå ¡éœ€è¦æœ‰æŠ¤åŸæ²³ã€‚</p>

<p>That moat can be various things. The moat in a businessâ€¦like our auto insurance business, GEICO, is low cost. I mean, people have to buy auto insurance so everyoneâ€™s gonna have one auto insurance policy per car basicallyâ€¦per driver. I canâ€™t sell them 20, but they have to buy 1. What are they gonna buy? They gonna buy onâ€¦base on service and cost. Most people will assume the service is fairly identical among companies or close enough. So weâ€™re going to do on cost! I gotta be the low-cost producer. Thatâ€™s my moat. My cost got further lower than the other guy? Iâ€™ve thrown a couple of sharks into the moat. All the time, if you got a wonderful castle, there are people out there are trying to attack it, taking away from you. I want a castle I can understand but I want a castle with a moat around it.</p>

<p><br /></p>

<p>30å¹´å‰ï¼Œä¼Šå£«æ›¼æŸ¯è¾¾çš„æŠ¤åŸæ²³å’Œå¯å£å¯ä¹çš„æŠ¤åŸæ²³ä¸€æ ·å®½ã€‚æˆ‘çš„æ„æ€æ˜¯å¦‚æœä½ æ‰“ç®—ç»™ä½ çš„6ä¸ªæœˆå¤§çš„å©´å„¿æ‹ç…§ç‰‡ç„¶åå¸Œæœ›20å¹´åï¼Œ50å¹´åèƒ½çœ‹ä¸€çœ‹ â€”â€” ä½ ä¸çŸ¥é“æœªæ¥çš„æ•ˆæœå¦‚ä½•å› ä¸ºä½ ä¸æ˜¯ä¸“ä¸šæ‘„å½±å¸ˆï¼Œæ‰€ä»¥ä½ ä¹Ÿä¸çŸ¥é“é‚£äº›20å¹´å‰ï¼Œ50å¹´å‰çš„ç…§ç‰‡çš„æ•ˆæœç©¶ç«Ÿå¥½ä¸å¥½ã€‚åœ¨ä½ å¿ƒä¸­ä½ å¸Œæœ›ä½ ç†æƒ³çš„ç›¸ç‰‡å…¬å¸æ˜¯æœ€é‡è¦çš„äº‹æƒ…ï¼Œå› ä¸ºä»–ä»¬æ‰¿è¯ºä½ ï¼Œä½ ä»Šå¤©æ‹ä¸‹æ¥çš„å¯¹ä½ æ¥è¯´é‡è¦çš„ä¸œè¥¿çš„ç…§ç‰‡åœ¨20å¹´ï¼Œ30å¹´ï¼Œ50å¹´åçœ‹èµ·æ¥ä¾ç„¶å¾ˆä¸é”™ã€‚å¯èƒ½æ˜¯ä½ çš„å®å®æˆ–è€…åˆ«çš„ã€‚å¥½å§ï¼ŒæŸ¯è¾¾åœ¨è¿‡å»çš„30å¹´åšçš„éå¸¸å¥½ â€”â€” ä»–ä»¬ç‹¬å äº†è¿™ä¸€ç‚¹ã€‚ä»–ä»¬æœ‰ç€æˆ‘è¯´çš„æ€æƒ³ä»½é¢ã€‚å¿˜äº†å¸‚åœºä»½é¢å§ã€‚æ€æƒ³ä»½é¢ã€‚</p>

<p>30 years ago, Eastman Kodakâ€™s moat was just as wide as Coca Colaâ€™s moat. I mean if you gonna take a picture of your six-month-old baby and youâ€™re gonna want to look at that picture 20 years from now, or youâ€™re gonna want to look at that 50 years from now â€“ you never got a chance because you are not professional photographer so youâ€™re gonna to evaluate whatâ€™s gonna look like 20 or 50 years ago. What is in your mind about that photography company is what counts because they are promising you that the pictures you take today is going to be terrific to look at 20 years, 30 years, 50 years from now, about something that is very important to you. May be your own child or whatever may be. Well, Kodak had that in spades 30 years ago â€“ they owned them. They had what I call â€œshare of mind.â€ Forget about share of market. Share of mind.</p>

