<p>Coca-Cola is associated with people being happy around the world where every place they are happy. Disney World, or Disneyland, or the World Cup will be it, or the Olympics, where people are happy. Happiness and Coke go together. Now you give me, I donâ€™t care how much money, and tell me Iâ€™m gonna do that with RC Cola around the world and have 5 billion people to have a favorable image in their mind about RC Cola? I canâ€™t get done. You know, you can fool aroundâ€¦you can do anything you wanted to. You can have price discounts on weekends, anything. But you are not gonna touch it. Thatâ€™s what you want to have in a business. Thatâ€™s the moat. You want that moat to widen. If you are Ceeâ€™s Candy, you want to do everything in the world to make sure that the experience, basically, of giving that gift leads to a favorable reaction. That means that whatâ€™s in the box. It means the person that sells it to you. Because all our business is done when we are terribly busy. I mean people come in those weeks before Christmas or on Valentineâ€™s day. There are long lines. Five oâ€™clock in the afternoon, some woman is selling the last person the last box of candy. That person has been waiting in line for maybe 20 or 30 customers. If the salesperson smiles at the last customer, our moat is widened. If she snarls at him, our moat is narrowed. We canâ€™t see it. Itâ€™s going on every day. But thatâ€™s the key to it. I mean, the total part of product delivery is having everything associated with the Ceeâ€™s Candy and something pleasant happening. Thatâ€™s what business is all about.</p>

