<p>Warren Buffett: Well, Salomon, like I said, I went into that because it was 9% security in 1987, September 1987, the Dow was up 35% that year. We had sold a lot of stuff, and I had a lot of money around I donâ€™tâ€¦it looked like to me that we are never getting any chance to do anything. So I took an attractive security form in a business I would never buy the common stock of it. I went in because of that. I think thatâ€™s generally a mistake. It worked out OK finally on that. But itâ€¦itâ€™s not what I should have been doing. I should haveâ€¦we should have waited, in which case, I could have bought more Coca-Cola a year later or thereabout. We should have bought Coke at the prices they were selling at. Even though it wasnâ€™t selling at a pretty price at the time. That was a mistake. At Long Term Capital, thatâ€™sâ€¦we have learned other businesses that are associated with securities over the years. One of them is arbitrage. I have done arbitrage for 45 years. Graham did it probably 30 years before that. Thatâ€™s a business. Unfortunately, I have to be near a phone, for I have toâ€¦I have to really run out of the office myself. Because it requires being more sort of market-attuned. I donâ€™t want to do that anymore so Iâ€¦unless a really big arbitrage situation came along and I understood. I wonâ€™t be doing much of that. But weâ€¦ I have probably been in 300 arbitrage situations at least in my life, or maybe more. Itâ€™s a good business. Perfectly good business.</p>

