<p>å·´è²ç‰¹ï¼šå¥½å§ï¼Œä¿æ´æ˜¯ä¸€ä¸ªéå¸¸å¥½çš„å…¬å¸ã€‚å¼ºå¤§çš„åˆ†é”€èƒ½åŠ›ï¼Œè®¸å¤šåç‰Œï¼Œå’Œå„ç§å…¶ä»–çš„ã€‚ä½†æ˜¯å¦‚æœä½ é—®æˆ‘ï¼Œå¦‚æœç°åœ¨éœ€è¦å°†æˆ‘å…¨å®¶äººçš„å‡€å€¼æŠ•èµ„ä¸€ä¸ªå…¬å¸ï¼Œå¹¶ä¸”ä»æ­¤ä»¥åå¿…é¡»ç¦»å¼€è‚¡å¸‚20å¹´ï¼Œæˆ‘ä¼šé€‰ä¿æ´è¿˜æ˜¯å¯å£å¯ä¹ï¼Ÿå®é™…ä¸Šï¼Œä¿æ´çš„äº§å“çº¿æ›´åŠ åˆ†æ•£åŒ–ã€‚ä½†æ˜¯æˆ‘å¯¹å¯ä¹æ¯”ä¿æ´æ›´æœ‰ä¿¡å¿ƒã€‚ä½†å¦‚æœæœ‰äººå‘Šè¯‰æˆ‘æˆ‘å¿…é¡»æŒæœ‰ä¿æ´çš„è‚¡ç¥¨20å¹´ï¼Œæˆ‘å¹¶ä¸ä¼šä¸æ»¡æ„ã€‚å®ƒåœ¨æˆ‘çš„å¤‡é€‰åå•é‡Œæ’åœ¨å‰5%ï¼Œå› ä¸ºè¿™ä¸ªå…¬å¸å¾ˆéš¾è¢«å‡»è´¥ã€‚</p>

<p>Warren: Well, Procter &amp; Gamble is goodâ€¦ a very very good business. Strong distribution capability, lots of brand name, and everything. But if you ask me, if Iâ€™m going to be away for 20 years, put all my familyâ€™s net worth in one business. Whatever Procter &amp; Gamble or Coke? Actually, Procter &amp; Gamble are a little moreâ€¦be more diversified among product lines. But I would feel sure of Coke than Procter &amp; Gamble. I wouldnâ€™t be unhappy if somebody told me I have to own Procter &amp; Gamble during a 20-year period. That would be in my top 5% because they are not going to get killed.</p>

<p><br /></p>

<p>ä½†æ˜¯ç›¸æ¯”ä¿æ´ï¼Œæˆ‘å¯¹å¯ä¹æœªæ¥20,30å¹´çš„å•ä½å¢é•¿ç‡æ›´æœ‰ä¿¡å¿ƒã€‚</p>

<p>But, I would feel better about the unit growth and pricing power of Coke over a 20 or 30 years than I would about Procter &amp; Gamble. Right now the pricing power might be tough. But if you think about a billion serving a day, an extra penny means $10 million a day, you know. We own 8% of it, thatâ€™s $800,000 a day for Berkshire Hathaway, if you get another penny out of this stuff. Doesnâ€™t seem impossible, does it? I mean, it worth another penny with it. Right now it would be a mistake to try to get it in most market. But overtime, Coke will make more per serving than it does now. 20 years from now I will guarantee you it will more per serving. It will be selling a whole lot more serving. I donâ€™t know how many of them or how much more, but I know that.</p>

<p>P&amp;Gâ€™s main products, I donâ€™t think they have the kind of dominance and they donâ€™t have the kind of unit growth. But they are good businesses, you know. I wouldnâ€™t be unhappy if you told me that I have to put my familyâ€™s net worth in P&amp;G and that was the only stock I can own. I would, you knowâ€¦I might prefer other names but there are a hundred other names I would prefer.</p>

<h3 id="å¦‚ä½•è¯„ä»·éº¦å½“åŠ³10545--10820">å¦‚ä½•è¯„ä»·éº¦å½“åŠ³ï¼ˆ1:05:45 â€“ 1:08:20ï¼‰</h3>

